SIMPLE: sneap
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sneap
<hw>Sneap</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Icel.
<ets>sneypa</ets> to dishonor, disgrace, chide, but also E.
<ets>snip</ets>, and <ets>snub</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To check;
to reprimand; to rebuke; to chide.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp.
Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To nip; to blast; to blight.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Biron is like an envious, <qex>sneaping</qex> frost.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sneap</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sneap
<hw>Sneap</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A reprimand; a rebuke.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My lord, I will not undergo this <qex>sneap</qex> without
reply.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sneathe</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Sneath</ent>⟦br⟧
